# Cursor Rules

- Use Next.js 15.3 App Router structure (`src/app`)
- Use TypeScript throughout the project
- Do not use pages/ directory or older Next.js routing
- All global wrappers (e.g., PrivyProvider) must go inside `src/providers`
- Place Privy configuration logic in `src/lib/privy.ts`
- Components like ConnectButton must go inside `src/components`
- All styling must use Tailwind CSS with classes, no inline styles
- Set up `tailwind.config.js` with correct content paths (`src/**/*.{ts,tsx}`)
- Avoid unnecessary abstraction or boilerplate â€” keep the template minimal and readable
- Do not use class components or legacy React patterns
- The template must be dark mode by default, no light mode toggle
- Assume .env.local will have `NEXT_PUBLIC_PRIVY_APP_ID`
- Add helpful placeholder text or TODOs if something is optional
